"title": "5775: abuse",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5775",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The deliberate misuse of gifts or privileges, and the insulting of individuals. Scripture stresses that neither God's gifts nor his people are to be abused.</p>\n<h2>The abuse of God and his people</h2>\n<h3>Of God himself</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:16\">2KI 19:16</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Of God's people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh4:1-Neh4:4\">NEH 4:1–4:4</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:4\">1PE 4:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:11\">MAT 5:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:13\">ACT 2:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:32\">ACT 17:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:6\">ACT 18:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:9\">REV 2:9</a></p>\n<h3>Of God's servants</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:13\">ACT 2:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:16\">2CH 36:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:6-Ps22:8\">PSA 22:6–22:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:7-Ps69:12\">PSA 69:7–69:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps123:3\">PSA 123:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer20:7\">JER 20:7</a></p>\n<h3>Of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:14\">LUK 16:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:11\">LUK 23:11</a></p>\n<h2>The abuse of Christian freedom is condemned</h2>\n<h3>Believers are required to resist sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:12\">ROM 6:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:14\">ROM 6:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:1-Heb12:2\">HEB 12:1–12:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:16-1John5:18\">1JN 5:16–5:18</a></p>\n<h3>Grace does not give believers the freedom to sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:1-Rom6:2\">ROM 6:1–6:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:15\">ROM 6:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:5-Rom3:8\">ROM 3:5–3:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:17-Gal2:21\">GAL 2:17–2:21</a></p>\n<h2>The dangers of abusing Christian freedom</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:9-1Cor8:12\">1CO 8:9–8:12</a> <em>becoming a stumbling-block to others</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:13\">GAL 5:13</a> <em>indulging oneself</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:16\">1PE 2:16</a> <em>as means of covering up evil</em></p>\n<h2>Examples of the abuse of Christian freedom</h2>\n<h3>Sexual excesses</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:1-1Cor5:2\">1CO 5:1–5:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:12-1Cor6:20\">1CO 6:12–6:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:20-Rev2:22\">REV 2:20–2:22</a></p>\n<h3>Abuse of giving</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:1-Acts5:2\">ACT 5:1–5:2</a></p>\n<h3>Abuse of the Lord's Supper</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:20-1Cor11:22\">1CO 11:20–11:22</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Falling back into sin</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:1-Rom6:2\">ROM 6:1–6:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:1\">HEB 12:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:8-1John1:10\">1JN 1:8–1:10</a></p>\n<h3>Disobedience towards God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:6\">EPH 5:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:8\">1PE 2:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:3-1John2:4\">1JN 2:3–2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:4\">1JN 3:4</a></p>\n<h3>Abuse of spiritual gifts</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:1-1Cor14:20\">1CO 14:1–14:20</a></p>\n<h3>Eating food sacrificed to idols</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:1-1Cor8:13\">1CO 8:1–8:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:14\">REV 2:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:20\">REV 2:20</a></p>",
